question:
District category contains Dormitory District, Cultural Heritage Site, and Arts District.
Supermarkets category contains Stop & Shop, and Sainsbury's.
Product category contains Kefir, Canned Corn, and Yogurt.
Ingredient category contains Evaporated Milk, Pepper, and Thyme.
The number of each Canned Corn 's Evaporated Milk equals 16.
The number of each Canned Corn 's Pepper equals 21 more than each Sainsbury's 's Product.
The number of each Sainsbury's 's Canned Corn equals 10 more than each Kefir 's Pepper.
The number of each Cultural Heritage Site 's Stop & Shop equals 16.
The number of each Yogurt 's Evaporated Milk equals each Arts District 's Sainsbury's.
The number of each Yogurt 's Thyme equals 0.
The number of each Dormitory District 's Sainsbury's equals 7.
The number of each Kefir 's Pepper equals 0 more than each Dormitory District 's Supermarkets.
The number of each Arts District 's Sainsbury's equals the sum of each Dormitory District 's Sainsbury's, each Sainsbury's 's Canned Corn, and each Kefir 's Pepper.
The number of each Sainsbury's 's Yogurt equals the sum of each Dormitory District 's Sainsbury's and each Sainsbury's 's Canned Corn.
The number of each Stop & Shop 's Yogurt equals the difference of each Cultural Heritage Site 's Stop & Shop and each Canned Corn 's Evaporated Milk.
How many Evaporated Milk does Yogurt have?
solution:
Define each Dormitory District 's Sainsbury's as i; So i = 7.
Define each Dormitory District 's Supermarkets as A; So A = i = 7.
Define each Kefir 's Pepper as o; So o = 0 + A = 0 + 7 = 7.
Define each Sainsbury's 's Canned Corn as L; So L = 10 + o = 10 + 7 = 17.
Define each Arts District 's Sainsbury's as n; B = i + o = 7 + 7 = 14; So n = L + B = 17 + 14 = 8.
Define each Yogurt 's Evaporated Milk as r; So r = n = 8.
